=====================================================================
EXERCISE LIBRARY — ORGANIZED BY MUSCLE GROUP
=====================================================================
How it works: When you pick a muscle (e.g. "chest") for a gym day,
the system searches ALL exercises below that muscle group and picks
the configured number. Compound exercises get priority (top EMG rank
first), then isolation exercises are shuffled for variety.

Tiers:
  BIG   = 4 exercises per session  (chest, back, legs)
  MID   = 3 exercises (shoulders), 2 exercises (biceps, triceps)
  SMALL = 2 exercises per session  (abs, neck, forearms, rear_delts, calves)

A random "bonus" small muscle is also auto-added each session.
